LAGOS  – Sir Charles Mbelede , the new Su­preme Knights of St Mulumba of Ni­geria has called on Parents of youth who suddenly become rich overnight to stop celebrating wealth that they don’t know the source of in order to curb the rising level of ritual killings in the country. Mbelede condemned the rate at which the killing of and harvesting of parts among desperate youth and advised them to be level-headed and law-abiding because money is not ev­erything. Mbelede made this appeal at the Thanksgiving Mass and grand re­ception organised to celebrate him as the Supreme Knight of honour of St. Mulumba on February 12, 2022 by the Lagos and Surulere Sub- Councils. Ogene’s Mother For Burial March 4 Robbers Kill UBTH Optometrist Doctor In Benin The knights further added that in order to counter the challenges of crime among the youth, the govern­ment must plan to tackle unemploy­ment that the country is faced with. The government must plan and en­sure that there is a good standard of living among the citizens, he said. He added, “That is why we Knights are to share our time, treasury and tal­ents for the betterment of mankind, to the glory of God. In a contemporary Nigerian soci­ety, we are faced with a lot of hassles. The Knights are to protect the faith, the church and the less-privileged. Right now, we are building houses for the less-privileged widows irre­spective of creeds. Thus far, we have built like twenty-five bungalows for widows. We also fight crimes and all forms of illegality, no matter how highly placed the person involved may be. We fight crimes through advocacy.”